<article class='nx-article'>
  <header>
    <h1>The Bowl Season Opens: Eight Can't-Miss Games Through December 19</h1>
    <p class="nx-tagline">From HBCU championships to coastal venues, the first wave of bowl games delivers underdog drama before the playoff chaos.</p>
  </header>
  <section class="nx-article__meta">
    <span class="nx-eyebrow">By Nexairi Sports · 9 min read</span>
  </section>
  <section class='nx-article__body'>
    <p>The bowl season kicks off with a slate of intriguing matchups featuring Group of Five contenders, HBCU pride, and holiday vibes. From Atlanta to Tampa, these games offer underdog stories, rivalries, and festive atmospheres before the playoff frenzy. Here's why casual fans should tune in for the opening games through December 19.</p>

    <h2>Cricket Celebration Bowl</h2>
    <p><strong>South Carolina State vs. Prairie View A&M</strong></p>
    <p><strong>December 13 (Saturday) · 12:00 PM ET · Mercedes-Benz Stadium, Atlanta, GA</strong></p>
    <p>This HBCU showdown pits MEAC's South Carolina State against SWAC's Prairie View A&M in the de facto black college football national championship. The game celebrates tradition with high-energy bands and pageantry that rivals any major bowl. Expect explosive plays from athletic squads hungry for glory. The Celebration Bowl, launched in 2015 as successor to the Pelican and Heritage Bowls, has delivered classics like North Carolina A&T's multiple wins and draws massive crowds to Atlanta.</p>

    <h2>Bucked Up LA Bowl Hosted by Gronk</h2>
    <p><strong>Boise State vs. Washington</strong></p>
    <p><strong>December 13 (Saturday) · 8:00 PM ET · SoFi Stadium, Inglewood, CA</strong></p>
    <p>Boise State's Mountain West grit clashes with Washington's Pac-12 experience in a West Coast primetime battle at glamorous SoFi Stadium. Both teams boast dynamic offenses capable of lighting up the scoreboard under the lights. It's a perfect nightcap to the bowl season opener with NFL-caliber talent on display. The LA Bowl, hosted by Rob Gronkowski since gaining sponsorship, brings Mountain West champs against top non-Power conference foes in Los Angeles' premier venue.</p>

    <h2>IS4S Salute to Veterans Bowl</h2>
    <p><strong>Troy vs. Jacksonville State</strong></p>
    <p><strong>December 16 (Tuesday) · 9:00 PM ET · Cramton Bowl, Montgomery, AL</strong></p>
    <p>Sun Belt rivals Troy and Jacksonville State renew an old rivalry in a game loaded with late-season drama and playoff-like intensity. Both programs have gritty defenses that could lead to a low-scoring thriller honoring military heroes. The historic Cramton Bowl adds atmosphere to this midweek gem. Originally the Camellia Bowl since 2014, the Salute to Veterans edition features tight finishes, with winners often decided in the fourth quarter.</p>

    <h2>StaffDNA Cure Bowl</h2>
    <p><strong>Old Dominion vs. South Florida</strong></p>
    <p><strong>December 17 (Wednesday) · 5:00 PM ET · Camping World Stadium, Orlando, FL</strong></p>
    <p>Old Dominion's Monarchs take on AAC's South Florida in sunny Orlando, where beach vibes meet football ambition for both rebuilding programs. Speedy offenses promise highlight-reel plays in this early bowl slot. A win boosts recruiting and momentum heading into next season. Since 2015, the Cure Bowl has raised over $6 million for cancer research, created by philanthropists to unite teams for a cause while delivering exciting matchups.</p>

    <h2>68 Ventures Bowl</h2>
    <p><strong>Louisiana vs. Delaware</strong></p>
    <p><strong>December 17 (Wednesday) · 8:30 PM ET · Hancock Whitney Stadium, Mobile, AL</strong></p>
    <p>Sun Belt's Louisiana Ragin' Cajuns face FCS-to-FBS mover Delaware in a Gulf Coast clash blending Cajun flair with Blue Hens' underdog fire. Expect a track meet with potent passing attacks under the Hancock Whitney lights. This game spotlights Mobile's hospitality and rising programs. Played annually since 1999 in Mobile, the 68 Ventures Bowl advances tourism and education while showcasing Sun Belt and AAC contenders.</p>

    <h2>Xbox Bowl</h2>
    <p><strong>Missouri State vs. Arkansas State</strong></p>
    <p><strong>December 18 (Thursday) · 9:00 PM ET · Ford Center at The Star, Frisco, TX</strong></p>
    <p>Transitioning Missouri State battles Sun Belt's Arkansas State in Frisco's state-of-the-art facility, perfect for a Thursday night shootout. Both teams feature young talent eager to make statements in prime time. Gaming sponsorship adds fun energy to this emerging rivalry. The Xbox Bowl marks a fresh addition to the postseason, pitting conference up-and-comers at the Dallas Cowboys' practice home for national exposure.</p>

    <h2>Myrtle Beach Bowl</h2>
    <p><strong>Kennesaw State vs. Western Michigan</strong></p>
    <p><strong>December 19 (Friday) · 11:00 AM ET · Brooks Stadium, Conway, SC</strong></p>
    <p>FCS newcomer Kennesaw State tests itself against MAC's Western Michigan in a beach-town morning kickoff full of sunshine and surprises. Newcomer energy versus veteran know-how sets up an unpredictable opener. Coastal Carolina's home turf brings rowdy fans to the party. Debuting in 2008, the Myrtle Beach Bowl thrives on Group of Five battles, offering vacation vibes and compelling undercard action.</p>

    <h2>Union Home Mortgage Gasparilla Bowl</h2>
    <p><strong>Memphis vs. NC State</strong></p>
    <p><strong>December 19 (Friday) · 2:30 PM ET · Raymond James Stadium, Tampa, FL</strong></p>
    <p>Memphis' high-flying attack meets NC State's Wolfpack defense in Tampa, where pirate-themed festivities amp up the stakes. Both 7-8 win teams play for pride and bowl swag like a giant treasure chest. Afternoon slot makes it family-friendly fun. Since 2018 at Raymond James, the Gasparilla Bowl (formerly Beef O'Brady's) delivers AAC-ACC clashes with Tampa's party atmosphere.</p>
  </section>
